**Event Information:**
- **Event Name:** AppSec Challenge
- **Organizer:** @Sketrik & @l4wke
- **Location:** Virtual/in-person at SAINTCON
- **Event Schedule:** 
  - **Start Time:** Tuesday - Noon
  - **End Time:** Friday - 9:00 AM
  - **Booth Hours:**
    - Tuesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
    - Wednesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
    - Thursday: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
    - Friday: 9:00 AM - 10:00 AM

**Description:**
The challenge focuses on finding and fixing vulnerabilities in source code. Participants are expected to:
- Clone the repository
- Identify and fix vulnerabilities
- Ensure unit tests pass
- Submit code to the scoring engine for points

**Unique Features:**
- The application consists of various microservices written in different languages.
- Participants may use automated tools for assistance.

**Rules:**
- Hacking the site or submission mechanism is forbidden.
- Submissions limited to specified files and maximum size of 4MB.
- One submission every 5 minutes per user.
- Prizes awarded to the top scorers.

**Resources:**
- Contestants are encouraged to visit the AppSec community for help and resources.

**Useful Links:**
- [AppSec Community](https://appsec.saintcon.community/)

